<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Equally" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Equally,</orth> 1) in the same manner, at the same time: <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.4.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 4, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 32</bibl>. In <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.213" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 213</bibl> Qq F<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>egally.</emph><lb />2) in the same proportion: <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.73" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.294" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 294</bibl>.
<lb />3) alike in weight or dignity: <cit><quote>you weigh e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 31</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>ne'er settled e., but high or low,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1139" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1139</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>